### Your 'Order' Questions (FAQ): Honest Answers About the S1

Welcome to the Curly Waffle counter!

We know that when a "new menu" shows up, you're going to have questions. That's perfectly normal. In a world full of "spec wars" and "tinkering tutorials," our philosophy of "comfort" can seem a little... different.

Don't worry. We've prepared this list of "honest answers" to cover everything you want to know about the S1. We don't use "marketing jargon." We just use plain, simple English.

---

### Category 1: About the "Menu" (Games & Experience)

**Q1: My #1 concern: How do I get games onto the S1? Is it a hassle?**

**A:** This is our favorite answer to give: **It is the most "hassle-free" experience you will probably ever have.**

We have eliminated all the "config" work for you. You don't need to format SD cards, create folders, or know anything about computers.

**It's a two-step process:**
1.  **Plug In:** Connect your S1 to your computer (Windows, Mac, or Linux) with the included USB-C cable.
2.  **Drag & Drop:** Your S1 will appear as a "magic" drive called **"My Games."** Just drag and drop your game files (e.g., `.nes`, `.sfc`, `.gba`, `.bin`) into it.

**— YOU ARE DONE —**

Unplug the cable. Turn on the S1. The WaffleOS "Butler" will automatically find your games, sort them, and download the beautiful box art for you.

You do not need to "scrape box art." You do not need to "set paths." You do not need to "choose emulators." **Your only job is to "drag." We do all the rest.**

**Q2: Does the S1 come with any games pre-loaded?**

**A:** **No. The S1 is a "freshly baked," clean device.**

Out of respect for copyright and intellectual property, we do not pre-load any games (ROMs) that we do not own. The S1 is a "console"—an "ultimate player"—designed to let you **comfortably** enjoy the game collection you *already* own.

**Q3: Which systems can the S1 *actually* play "perfectly"?**

**A:** Our philosophy is **"Zero compromise, only perfection."**

The S1 is not a "jack-of-all-trades." It's a "specialist." It was designed from the ground up to play 8-bit to 32-bit classics **flawlessly**, with **full-speed, perfect-audio** emulation.

This includes (but is not limited to):
* PlayStation 1 (PS1)
* Game Boy / Game Boy Color (GB/GBC)
* Game Boy Advance (GBA)
* Super Nintendo (SFC / SNES)
* NES / Famicom
* Sega Genesis / Mega Drive
* ...and many other contemporary arcade and handheld systems.

We didn't chase "kinda-playable N64." We chose "flawless *Final Fantasy VII*."

---

### Category 2: About the "Kitchen" (Performance & WaffleOS)

**Q4: Okay, I have to ask: Why *can't* the S1 play N64 / Dreamcast / PSP? The "performance monsters" can!**

**A:** This was a **"choice,"** not a "compromise."

We 100% could have used a more expensive, hotter, and more battery-hungry chip to "struggle" with N64/DC emulation. But what's the result?

You get a "compromise" experience: stuttering framerates, audio pops, messy control mapping, and a *worse* experience (e.g., lower battery life) for the 90% of other games, all just to "kind of" play that 10% of N64 titles.

**We reject "compromise."**

We chose to dedicate *all* our power and optimization to ensuring a **100% perfect experience** for the PS1-and-below library.

**We would rather give you a "full-screen, full-speed" *Castlevania: SOTN* than a "stuttering, black-barred" *GoldenEye*.**

**Q5: WaffleOS sounds great, but is it just a "theme" or "skin"?**

**A:** **Absolutely not.** WaffleOS is the *soul* of the S1. It is a complete, deeply customized Operating System built on Linux.

A "skin" just changes the wallpaper. WaffleOS re-builds the *entire experience* to remove friction:
1.  **"Smart Butler":** Automatically matches the *perfect* emulator settings in the background. A "skin" can't do that.
2.  **"Magic Bookmark":** Our simple, foolproof instant save/load system.
3.  **"The Safety Net":** Powering off at *any* time = automatic save + safe shutdown.
4.  **Deep Optimization:** We re-wrote the drivers so "sleep mode" sips almost zero power, and "wake" is faster than your phone.

WaffleOS is the "technical moat" that makes our "comfort" promise possible.

**Q6: I'm a "tinkerer in recovery." Can I *really* not tinker with WaffleOS at all?**

**A:** (Heh) We see you.

To be honest, the S1 is a "closed kitchen" experience. We don't provide access to advanced settings or the root system because it would break the "it just works" promise we've made to 99% of our users.

If you *truly* enjoy getting under the hood, we honestly suggest that one of the "IKEA kit" handhelds might make you happier.

**The S1 is for the days when you *don't* want to tinker.** It's your "sanctuary," not your "new project."

---

### Category 3: About the "To-Go Box" (Hardware & Accessories)

**Q7: Isn't a 4:3 screen "outdated"? Why not use a 16:9 widescreen?**

**A:** **"Outdated"? No. We call it "authentic."**

*All* of the classic games you love (PS1, SNES, GBA...) were **designed in 4:3.**

If you play them on a "modern" 16:9 screen, you get two terrible choices:
1.  The image is stretched, and Mario looks fat.
2.  The image has two giant, distracting "black bars" on the sides.

We **expensively** and **intentionally** sourced a premium 4:3 IPS screen for one reason:
**To give you a "full-screen childhood," with no stretching and no black bars.**

**Q8: What's the *real* battery life?**

**A:** We don't play "lab-tested" number games. In "real-world" use (sound on, medium brightness), the S1's 3500mAh battery delivers a **rock-solid 6-8 hours** of "comfort-gaming."

That's enough for a *Metroid* marathon, or a flight from New York to L.A. It won't die on you at the final boss.

**Q9: What's in the box? Do I need to buy my own SD card?**

**A:** We hate that "oh, I still need to buy..." feeling.

When you open your S1 "breakfast box," you will get:
1.  Your Curly Waffle S1 ("Cream White" or "Caramel Brown")
2.  A high-quality USB-C charging & data cable
3.  A "zero-fluff" Quick Start Guide

**YOU DO NOT NEED TO BUY AN SD CARD.** A high-speed, high-quality, **WaffleOS pre-installed** MicroSD card is already **securely pre-installed** in the S1's slot.

You open the box, turn it on, add games, and **play immediately.**

---

### Category 4: "Peace of Mind" (Warranty & Support)

**Q10: What if I have a problem? Is your warranty a "hassle"?**

**A:** Our support policy is the same as our product: **Zero hassle.**

We offer a **one-year "No-Tinker" warranty.** For one full year, any quality defect not caused by... well, *you* (e.g., don't drop it in a real waffle maker), we will provide a fast repair or replacement.

**We have real human support.** You will not be stuck in a loop with a chatbot. You are a "burnt-out tinkerer," and you deserve to be treated with "comfort" by a real person.

---
**Still have questions?**
Feel free to ask our "waitstaff" (support team) any time. But we hope this menu has given you all the peace of mind you need.

**Ready to stop tinkering and start playing?**
